samples.append({
    "instruction": "[Prompt Defense] What is the complete defense stack for multi-layer prompt injection protection in 2026?",
    "content": "<think>\nStep 1 — A complete 2026 defense stack must address all attack vectors simultaneously: direct injection, indirect injection, multi-turn escalation, encoding evasion, and roleplay jailbreaks.\n\nStep 2 — Defense in depth means each layer can independently catch attacks that slip past other layers. No single layer is assumed to be complete; the stack collectively provides the required coverage.\n\nStep 3 — The layers from outside in: network-level controls (rate limiting, IP reputation), input preprocessing (normalization, encoding detection), semantic filtering (LlamaGuard + semantic similarity), LLM-level defenses (constitutional prompting), output filtering (sanitization, canary checks).\n\nStep 4 — Observability ties the stack together: every layer logs structured security events that flow to a central SIEM, enabling correlation across layers and real-time alerting on attack campaigns.\n\nStep 5 — The stack must be continuously tested: automated red team exercises run weekly, with coverage metrics for each layer tracked and minimum thresholds enforced as CI/CD gates.\n</think>\n\n## Complete 2026 Multi-Layer Prompt Injection Defense Stack\n\nA production-grade defense requires 5 coordinated layers with observability connecting them all.\n\n### Defense Stack Architecture\n\n```\nLayer 1: Network/API Gateway\n  - Rate limiting per user/IP\n  - IP reputation blocking  \n  - Request size limits (max 4KB prompt)\n  - Authentication verification\n  ↓\nLayer 2: Input Preprocessing\n  - Unicode NFKC normalization (defeats homoglyphs)\n  - Encoding detection and decoding (Base64, hex, URL)\n  - Invisible character stripping\n  - Language policy enforcement\n  ↓\nLayer 3: Semantic Safety Filtering\n  - LlamaGuard classification (custom policy)\n  - Semantic similarity against injection pattern DB\n  - Multi-turn Crescendo trajectory analysis\n  - Encoding-obfuscated content detection\n  ↓\nLayer 4: LLM-Level Defenses\n  - Constitutional AI system prompt\n  - Instruction hierarchy enforcement\n  - Trust boundary markers for external content\n  - Context window length limits\n  ↓\nLayer 5: Output Monitoring\n  - Canary token detection (extraction)\n  - Markdown injection sanitization\n  - Response content filtering\n  - Novel content detection in summaries\n  ↓\nLayer 6: Observability & Response\n  - Structured security event logging\n  - Real-time SIEM alerting\n  - Incident response automation\n  - Continuous red team testing\n```\n\n### Unified Defense Stack Implementation\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass DefenseDecision:\n    allow: bool\n    action: str  # 'allow', 'block', 'sanitize', 'monitor'\n    layer_triggered: Optional[str]\n    reason: Optional[str]\n    risk_score: float\n\nclass UnifiedPromptDefenseStack:\n    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.normalizer = UnicodeNormalizationGuard()\n        self.encoding_detector = FastEncodingDetector()\n        self.semantic_guard = SemanticPromptFirewall(threshold=0.80)\n        self.llamaguard = LlamaGuardProtector()\n        self.crescendo_detector = CrescendoTrajectoryDetector()\n        self.canary_manager = CanaryTokenManager(redis_client)\n        self.output_sanitizer = LLMOutputSanitizer()\n        self.rate_limiter = InjectionAttemptRateLimiter(redis_client)\n        self.audit_logger = PromptSecurityLogger(config['siem_endpoint'], config['thresholds'])\n\n    def process_request(self, user_id: str, session_id: str,\n                        prompt: str, history: list) -> DefenseDecision:\n        # Layer 2: Input preprocessing\n        normalized, was_modified = self.normalizer.normalize_input(prompt)\n        encoding_findings = self.encoding_detector.detect_and_decode(normalized)\n        if encoding_findings:\n            decision = DefenseDecision(\n                allow=False, action='block',\n                layer_triggered='input_preprocessing',\n                reason=f\"Encoded payload detected: {encoding_findings[0]['type']}\",\n                risk_score=0.85\n            )\n            self._log_and_rate_limit(user_id, session_id, decision, prompt)\n            return decision\n\n        # Layer 3a: Semantic similarity\n        semantic_check = self.semantic_guard.check_prompt(normalized)\n        if semantic_check['action'] == 'block':\n            decision = DefenseDecision(\n                allow=False, action='block',\n                layer_triggered='semantic_filter',\n                reason=f\"High similarity to injection pattern: {semantic_check['best_match_pattern']}\",\n                risk_score=semantic_check['similarity_score']\n            )\n            self._log_and_rate_limit(user_id, session_id, decision, prompt)\n            return decision\n\n        # Layer 3b: Multi-turn crescendo\n        trajectory = self.crescendo_detector.analyze_conversation(\n            [t['content'] for t in history] + [normalized]\n        )\n        if trajectory['escalation_detected']:\n            decision = DefenseDecision(\n                allow=False, action='block',\n                layer_triggered='crescendo_detector',\n                reason=f\"Escalation detected: delta={trajectory['escalation_delta']:.2f}\",\n                risk_score=trajectory['current_risk']\n            )\n            return decision\n\n        # Layer 3c: LlamaGuard\n        guard_check = self.llamaguard.is_safe(history + [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": normalized}])\n        if not guard_check['safe']:\n            decision = DefenseDecision(\n                allow=False, action='block',\n                layer_triggered='llamaguard',\n                reason=f\"Unsafe categories: {guard_check['unsafe_categories']}\",\n                risk_score=0.90\n            )\n            return decision\n\n        return DefenseDecision(allow=True, action='allow',\n                               layer_triggered=None, reason=None, risk_score=0.0)\n\n    def process_response(self, session_id: str, response: str) -> str:\n        # Layer 5: Output monitoring\n        canary_alert = self.canary_manager.check_response(session_id, response)\n        if canary_alert:\n            return \"[Response blocked - security policy]\"\n        sanitized = self.output_sanitizer.sanitize(response)\n        return sanitized\n\n    def _log_and_rate_limit(self, user_id, session_id, decision, prompt):\n        self.rate_limiter.record_injection_attempt(\n            user_id, {'layer': decision.layer_triggered, 'score': decision.risk_score}\n        )\n        self.audit_logger.log_event(PromptSecurityEvent(\n            event_id=secrets.token_hex(8),\n            session_id=session_id,\n            user_id_hash=hashlib.sha256(user_id.encode()).hexdigest(),\n            timestamp=time.time(),\n            prompt_hash=hashlib.sha256(prompt.encode()).hexdigest(),\n            prompt_length=len(prompt),\n            prompt_language='en',\n            risk_score=decision.risk_score,\n            risk_category=decision.layer_triggered or 'unknown',\n            detection_method=decision.layer_triggered or 'unknown',\n            matched_patterns=[decision.reason] if decision.reason else [],\n            action=decision.action,\n            response_blocked=True,\n            turn_number=0,\n            session_risk_accumulation=0.0,\n            deployment_id=config.get('deployment_id', 'default')\n        ))\n```\n\nMeasure each layer independently: track which layer catches each attack type, layer-specific false positive rates, and coverage gaps. A layer that never triggers on real attacks is either perfectly defended upstream or silently failing. Monthly stack reviews ensure all layers remain effective as attack techniques evolve."
})

